This paper deals with online learning and bandit problems, which are typically studied in the machine learning and artificial intelligence communities (cs.LG, cs.AI). The Plackett-Luce model is a popular choice model in preference learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and falls under the data mining category (cs.DM). The paper also discusses sample complexity and information theory, which are relevant to the information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC) categories.
